1
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:06,920
DOCTOR: As you come into this
world, something else is also born.

2
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:13,520
You begin your life,
and it begins a journey,

3
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,000
towards you.

4
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:18,280
It moves slowly,
but it never stops.

5
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:23,320
Wherever you go,
whatever path you take,

6
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,040
it will follow.

7
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:28,000
Never faster, never slower.

8
00:00:28,080 --> 00:00:30,560
Always coming.

9
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:34,080
You will run, it will walk.

10
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:38,000
You will rest. it will not.

11
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:43,360
One day, you will linger
in the same place too long.

12
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:48,160
You will sit too still
or slip too deep.

13
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:53,640
And when, too late,
you rise to go,

14
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:59,560
you will notice a second
shadow next to yours.

15
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:03,480
Your life will then be over.

16
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:04,960
(MACHINE POWERING UP)

17
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:06,360
(MAN GROANS)

18
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:17,360
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

19
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,520
(COUGHING)

20
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:22,920
(WHEEZING)

21
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:32,160
(DOOR HISSING)

22
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:43,800
(RAVEN CAWING)

23
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,240
DOCTOR: If you think
because she's dead I'm weak,

24
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:05,640
then you understand
very little.

25
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:08,880
If you were any part of killing
her, and you're not afraid,

26
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:11,440
then you understand
nothing at all.

27
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:14,280
So for your own sake
understand this...

28
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:16,240
I am the Doctor.

29
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:20,040
I'm coming to find you,
and I will never, ever stop.

30
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:23,120
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

31
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,560
The equipment in that room,

32
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:40,880
it's consistent with an
augmented ultra-long range teleport.

33
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:45,560
So I'm not more than a single
light year from where I was.

34
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:48,160
And I'm in the same time zone.

35
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,600
When the sun sets,

36
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:01,360
I'll be able to establish an
exact position by the stars,

37
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:04,000
then you'll have a choice.

38
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:07,040
Come out, show yourself,

39
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:08,800
or keep on hiding.

40
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,600
Clara said I shouldn't
take revenge.

41
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:15,920
You should know
I don't always listen.

42
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,440
Oh, what's this?

43
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:25,760
What, are you gardeners?
I hate gardening!

44
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:32,800
What sort of a person has
a power-complex about flowers?

45
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,920
It's dictatorship
for inadequates.

46
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,320
Or to put it in another way,
it's dictatorship.

47
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:39,680
Come on!
(CLAPPING) Chop, chop!

48
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:43,280
The Doctor will see you now.
Show me what you've got!

49
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,720
I just watched
my best friend die in agony,

50
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,000
my day can't get any worse.

51
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:48,200
Let's see what
we can do about yours.

52
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:49,720
(STATIC)

53
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,280
(GASPS)

54
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:28,960
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

55
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,000
(INSECT BUZZING)

56
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,560
(THUDDING CONTINUES)

57
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,720
(BREATHING ANXIOUSLY)

58
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:13,840
(GRUNTING)

59
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,280
I know you.

60
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,800
I've seen you before.

61
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,960
I used to know a trick.

62
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,720
Back when I was young
and telepathic.

63
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:37,520
Clearly, you can't make
an actual psychic link with a door

64
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,200
for one very obvious reason.

65
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:41,120
They're notoriously cross.

66
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,160
I mean, imagine
life as a door.

67
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,920
People keep pushing past you,

68
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,240
all of the knocking,
but it's never for you,

69
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,400
and you get
locked up every night.

70
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,200
So if you are

71
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:53,320
just a little bit nice...

72
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,400
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

73
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,080
See, Clara?

74
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:58,920
I've still got it.

75
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,000
(SIGHS)

76
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,240
Right. (STAMMERING)

77
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,120
Uh...

78
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,840
I can't actually
see a way out of this.

79
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:18,080
Finally run out of corridor,
there's a life summed up.

80
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,160
(INHALES)

81
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,080
This isn't you.

82
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,960
I'm scared.

83
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:28,400
I just realised that
I'm actually scared of dying.

84
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,680
Something I said?

85
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:36,280
What did I say?

86
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,640
Why did you stop?

87
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,520
(RUMBLING)

88
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,360
(SNIFFING)

89
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:08,800
Old. Very old.
Possibly very, very old.

90
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,760
When I was a very little boy
there was an old lady who died.

91
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:21,440
(POPS) They covered her in veils,
but it was a hot, sunny day,

92
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:24,520
and the flies came. It gave me
nightmares for years.

93
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,720
So who's been
stealing my nightmares?

94
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:29,240
What am I here for?

95
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:33,160
And you've known about me
for a very long time, right?

96
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:39,040
So, what is it?

97
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:42,320
Is it a trap?

98
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,280
Is it a prison?

99
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:46,800
No!

100
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,960
Is it a torture chamber?

101
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,640
Am I right?

102
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:55,680
Somebody really
should know better.

103
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:58,600
Anyone who can put
all of this together,

104
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,680
and steal my bad dreams,

105
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:01,960
they should know better.

106
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:04,600
The secrets I have...

107
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,080
No chance, not telling, not me!

108
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,280
I told you I was scared of dying,

109
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:12,080
and I wasn't lying either.

110
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,480
Advantage, me.

111
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:19,480
Because you won't
see this coming!

112
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:26,920
Sorry I'm late.

113
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,240
Jumped out of a window.

114
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,520
Sudden death.

115
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,160
Don't you want to know how I survived?

116
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,960
Go on, ask me.

117
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:38,200
No! Of course I had to jump!

118
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:40,120
The first rule of being
interrogated is

119
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:43,000
that you are the only
irreplaceable person

120
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,280
in the torture chamber.

121
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:47,520
The room is yours, so work it.

122
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,200
If they're going to
threaten you with death,

123
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:52,280
show them who's boss.
Die faster!

124
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,280
And you've seen me do that
more often than most.

125
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,960
Isn't that right, Clara?

126
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:06,160
Rule one of dying, don't.

127
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,880
Rule two, slow down.

128
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:12,520
You've got the rest of your life.

129
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:15,000
The faster you think,
the slower it will pass.

130
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,080
Concentrate!

131
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,360
Assume you're going to survive.

132
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,080
Always assume that.

133
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,520
Imagine you've already survived.

134
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,320
There's a storeroom
in your mind.

135
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:27,040
Lock the door and think.

136
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,440
This is my storeroom.

137
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,640
I always imagine
that I'm back in my Tardis.

138
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:34,640
Showing off. Telling you

139
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,880
how I escaped, making you laugh.

140
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:39,000
That's what I'm doing right now.

141
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:42,160
I am falling, Clara.

142
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,200
I'm dying.

143
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:48,480
And I'm going to explain
to you how I survived.

144
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:52,040
Can't wait to hear what I say.

145
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,800
I'm nothing without an audience.

146
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,520
One hope, salt.

147
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:04,600
I thought I smelt it earlier,
when I broke the window, I'm sure.

148
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:07,680
Salty air. This castle
is standing in the sea!

149
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,920
Diving into water
from a great height

150
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,760
is no guarantee of survival.

151
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:16,520
I need to know exactly
how far I'm going to fall, and how fast.

152
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,800
Why do you think I threw the stool?

153
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,360
Fall time to impact.

154
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:24,800
(WATER SPLASHING)

155
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,160
DOCTOR: Seven seconds!/

156
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:28,040
Because you won't see this coming!

157
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,160
The wind resistance of the stool,

158
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:32,000
the atmospheric density,

159
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,680
the strength of the local gravity.

160
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,320
Am I spoiling the magic?

161
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,880
I work with this stuff, you know.

162
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:40,880
Should hit the water in about...

163
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,680
.02 seconds.

164
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:48,360
The chances of remaining
conscious are...

165
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:16,240
(TARDIS POWERING UP)

166
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:30,080
(SCRIBBLING ON CHALKBOARD)

167
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:41,600
Can't I just sleep?

168
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,640
(SCRIBBLING CONTINUES)

169
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:53,640
Do I have to know everything?

170
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:56,000
(SCRIBBLING CONTINUES)

171
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:03,640
Clara...

172
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,960
I can't lose.

173
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:36,600
(PANTING)

174
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:01,240
(FIRE CRACKLING)

175
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,240
(DOOR CREAKING)

176
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:45,160
It keeps coming, Clara!

177
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:48,880
Wherever I go, it follows, why?
Why does it do that?

178
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:53,480
Always the teacher.
What's the right question then?

179
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:54,840
(SCRIBBLING ON
CHALKBOARD CONTINUES)

180
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:03,720
It's following me.

181
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:08,760
Wherever I go, it's tracking me.

182
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:11,800
Slowly though, scary lurching.

183
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,920
Scary.

184
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:20,640
These screens everywhere,

185
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:23,640
it's showing me exactly
where it is all the time.

186
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:26,200
How far it's got, how near.

187
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:32,480
Because it's trying to scare me,

188
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:33,960
putting its breath on my neck.

189
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:35,720
That's the point.
That's what it's doing.

190
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,920
This is theatre!

191
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,160
It's all about fear.

192
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:41,760
A working hypothesis.

193
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:45,280
We're in a fully-automated
haunted house, a mechanical maze.

194
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:47,160
(CLATTERING)

195
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:56,120
It's a killer puzzle box
designed to scare me to death.

196
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,240
And I'm trapped inside it.

197
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:00,400
(CHUCKLES)

198
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:03,160
Must be Christmas.

199
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:04,920
(DISTANT CLANGING)

200
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:47,960
(DOOR CREAKS)

201
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,440
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

202
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:27,200
Another spade.

203
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:28,920
Someone wants me to take it.

204
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:31,200
What do you think, Clara?

205
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:33,480
Someone trying to give me a hint?

206
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:34,840
What would you do?

207
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:37,960
Yes, yes, of course you would.

208
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,680
Which, let's be honest,
is what killed you.

209
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:46,480
So...

210
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:49,400
Someone is trying to tell me that
there's something important

211
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:51,200
buried in this garden.

212
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:54,400
That's almost the first thing
they tried to tell me.

213
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:55,480
It could be a trick.

214
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:58,840
It could be one of
my predecessors.

215
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:01,000
Because I'm not
the first prisoner here, am I?

216
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,040
(ECHOING) All those skulls!

217
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,280
Wonder where they all went wrong.

218
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:13,920
A building this height,

219
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:16,240
a creature that slow, so what?

220
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:20,080
An hour.

221
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:29,120
(GRUNTING AND PANTING)

222
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,120
(FLY BUZZING)

223
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:05,720
(EXHALES)

224
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:11,160
(FLY CONTINUES BUZZING)

225
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:16,760
(SCREECHING)

226
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:28,600
(RATTLING)

227
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,280
Fifty-seventh time, you lose.

228
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,400
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

229
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:41,880
(CREATURE HISSING)

230
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,240
So...

231
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,240
It can set traps.

232
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:54,720
That's okay.

233
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:57,080
I'm good at traps.

234
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,200
So where're you off to?

235
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,280
Only one way in and one way out.

236
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:23,000
Well, seeing as you're going.

237
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:37,560
(GRUNTING)

238
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,680
(EXHALES)

239
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:05,600
No, no, that's not right.

240
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:16,960
(METAL SCRAPING)

241
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,440
(SPADE CLUNKS)

242
00:23:50,840 --> 00:23:52,280
(FLY BUZZING)

243
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:56,760
-(SCREECHING)
-(SCREAMS)

244
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,080
Well, that was another close one,

245
00:24:02,160 --> 00:24:03,360
or it would've been

246
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,400
once I've been
and gotten myself out of it.

247
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:07,560
So how am I going to do that?

248
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,480
Come on, teacher, ask me questions.

249
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:12,600
(SCRIBBLING ON CHALKBOARD)

250
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:19,360
I'm actually scared of dying.

251
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:22,800
(SCRIBBLING CONTINUES)

252
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:27,400
The truth, yes.

253
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:28,600
But not any old truth, Clara.

254
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:30,680
This whole place is
designed to terrify me.

255
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:32,680
I'm being interrogated.

256
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:37,240
It's not just truth it wants,
that's not enough,

257
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:40,080
it's confession.

258
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:46,520
I have to tell truths
I've never told before.

259
00:24:48,040 --> 00:24:50,120
That's the only thing
that stops it.

260
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,880
You see the problem is,

261
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:01,840
Clara...

262
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:08,840
...there are truths
that I can never tell.

263
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,840
Not for anything.

264
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:17,560
But I'm scared and I'm alone.

265
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:19,760
Alone...

266
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:24,040
And very, very scared.

267
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:32,680
I confess.

268
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,960
I didn't leave Gallifrey
because I was bored,

269
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:36,760
that was a lie,
it's always been a lie!

270
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:37,840
(GASPS)

271
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:43,080
Not enough? You want more?

272
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:48,640
I was scared.
I ran because I was scared.

273
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,200
Is that what you want me to say?

274
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:52,440
Is that true enough for you?

275
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:04,840
(WIND WHOOSHING)

276
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:02,160
(CLOCK TICKING)

277
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:03,560
DOCTOR: It's funny.

278
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:07,320
The day you lose someone
isn't the worst,

279
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:09,880
at least you've got something to do.

280
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:14,600
It's all the days they stay dead.

281
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,400
-(FLIES BUZZING)
-(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

282
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:27,280
Fifty-seven minutes.

283
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:34,440
This is how
my world works, Clara.

284
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:36,160
I tick off the seconds as they pass.

285
00:27:36,240 --> 00:27:37,240
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

286
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:39,120
My life is a countdown.

287
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:43,680
If I draw the creature to
one extreme of the castle,

288
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:47,360
and I run to the other extreme...

289
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:50,880
I can earn myself
a maximum of 82 minutes.

290
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,240
(PANTING)

291
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:58,280
Eighty-two minutes to eat,
sleep and work.

292
00:27:58,360 --> 00:28:02,200
My work is finding Room 12.

293
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:04,000
The castle wants me to.

294
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:05,600
It's luring me.

295
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:13,600
The numbering
ls a bit confused.

296
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:16,920
As if the rooms
are all jumbled up.

297
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:19,960
Maybe they move around.

298
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:24,520
I saw the whole castle move...

299
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,640
...when I made the creature stop.

300
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:37,120
Every room,
if I leave it long enough,

301
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:39,920
reverts to its condition
at the moment I arrived.

302
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:44,320
It tidies up after itself.

303
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:47,320
Automated room service.

304
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:58,360
I think this whole place
is inside a closed energy loop,

305
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:00,240
constantly recycling.

306
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:03,440
Or maybe I'm in hell.

307
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:06,320
That's okay.
I'm not scared of hell.

308
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:08,960
It's just heaven for bad people.

309
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:14,080
But how long
will I have to be here?

310
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:20,280
Forever.

311
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:24,000
(CLANGS)

312
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:30,000
It's always coming.

313
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:31,840
-(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)
-Always closer.

314
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,200
The countdown never stops.

315
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:37,760
But the countdown to what?

316
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:48,880
There are two events in everybody's
life that nobody remembers.

317
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:51,960
Two moments experienced
by every living thing.

318
00:29:53,360 --> 00:29:55,760
Yet no one remembers
anything about them

319
00:30:00,760 --> 00:30:05,280
Nobody remembers being born
and nobody remembers dying.

320
00:30:08,080 --> 00:30:12,200
Is that why we always
stare into the eye sockets of a skull?

321
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:14,920
Because we're asking,
"What was it like?

322
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:17,200
"Does it hurt?

323
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:19,200
"Are you still scared?”

324
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:24,680
DOCTOR: "Bird"?

325
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:27,080
What's a bird got to do with it?

326
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:28,600
Are there birds here?

327
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:32,320
(CLANGING)

328
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:35,280
(WIND WHOOSHING)

329
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:10,600
DOCTOR: There's something
I'm missing, Clara,

330
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:12,920
and I think it's something terrible.

331
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:26,560
(THUDS)

332
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:56,760
Hello?

333
00:31:57,760 --> 00:31:59,560
Hello? Is there someone there?
Hello!

334
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:11,480
DOCTOR: It's a trap, Clara.

335
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:13,160
A lure and a trap.

336
00:32:24,960 --> 00:32:27,120
I'm following bread crumbs
laid out for me.

337
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:33,760
This is somebody's game.

338
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:37,440
And I can't stop playing it.

339
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:39,920
A game everybody else has lost.

340
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:43,320
I know how to move
that wall, Clara.

341
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:45,600
So long as I don't
run out of confessions.

342
00:32:46,280 --> 00:32:47,520
What I really want to know is...

343
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:51,160
Who's been playing
about with the stars?

344
00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:53,560
-They're all in the wrong places.
-(FLY BUZZING)

345
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:55,120
For this time zone, anyway.

346
00:32:56,760 --> 00:32:59,800
No! I didn't time travel to get here.

347
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,600
I can feel time travel.

348
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:02,880
If I didn't know better,

349
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:06,440
I'd say I've travelled
7,000 years into the future.

350
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:09,280
But I do know better.

351
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:11,960
So who moved the stars?

352
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:18,960
Behind me.

353
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:21,200
(FLY BUZZING)

354
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,800
Long before the Time War,

355
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,560
the Time Lords knew
it was coming.

356
00:33:29,080 --> 00:33:30,680
Like a storm on the wind.

357
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:33,720
There were many
prophecies and stories.

358
00:33:33,800 --> 00:33:35,920
Legends before the fact.

359
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:40,440
One of them was about
a creature called the Hybrid.

360
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:44,880
Half Dalek, half Time Lord.

361
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:46,520
The ultimate warrior.

362
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:48,720
But whose side will it be on?

363
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:51,200
Would it bring peace
or destruction?

364
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:54,000
Was it real or a fantasy?

365
00:33:54,600 --> 00:33:59,200
I confess,
I know the Hybrid is real.

366
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:01,960
I know where it is and what it is.

367
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:04,840
I confess I'm afraid.

368
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:10,760
(RUMBLING)

369
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:27,760
(PANTING)

370
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:41,240
(CLOCK TICKING)

371
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:47,240
Of course!

372
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:49,760
The last square on the board.

373
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,840
What else would it be?

374
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:55,880
The Tardis.

375
00:35:55,960 --> 00:35:57,400
One confession away.

376
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:01,840
(WHIRRING)

377
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:04,600
Spantium.

378
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:08,320
Four-hundred times
harder than diamond.

379
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:12,960
Twenty feet thick.

380
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:18,560
The way out.

381
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:24,400
Bird.

382
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:37,960
That's when I remember!

383
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:42,320
Always then! Always then!

384
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,600
It was exactly there!

385
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,840
I can't keep doing this, Clara.

386
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:52,880
I can't!

387
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:54,840
Why is it always me?

388
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,800
Why is it never
anybody else's turn?

389
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:58,000
(SCRIBBLING ON CHALKBOARD)

390
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:04,400
Can't I just lose?

391
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:05,600
Just this once!

392
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:09,520
Easy. It would be easy.

393
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:12,320
It will be so easy.

394
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:13,480
Just tell them.

395
00:37:13,560 --> 00:37:15,960
Just tell,
whoever wants to know

396
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:17,320
all about the Hybrid.

397
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:22,800
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

398
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:31,680
I can't keep doing this!

399
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:33,880
I can't!

400
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:37,480
I can't always do this!

401
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:39,000
It's not fair!

402
00:37:39,080 --> 00:37:42,240
Clara, it's just not fair!
Why can't I just lose?

403
00:37:48,120 --> 00:37:49,640
But I can remember, Clara.

404
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:52,600
You don't understand.

405
00:37:53,600 --> 00:37:55,040
I can remember it all.

406
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:57,280
Every time.

407
00:38:02,120 --> 00:38:03,800
And you'll still be gone.

408
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,320
Whatever I do,

409
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:16,160
you still won't be there.

410
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:24,600
CLARA: Doctor.

411
00:38:26,120 --> 00:38:28,800
You are not the only person
who ever lost someone.

412
00:38:29,720 --> 00:38:31,360
It's the story of everybody.

413
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:34,760
Get over it. Beat it.

414
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:37,720
Break free.

415
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:45,120
Doctor, it's time.

416
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:51,040
Get up, off your arse,

417
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:54,280
and win.

418
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:00,680
(FLY BUZZING)

419
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:02,960
Hello, again.

420
00:39:03,040 --> 00:39:04,840
No more confessions. Sorry.

421
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:12,600
But I will tell you the truth.

422
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:25,760
(GRUNTS AND SCREAMS)

423
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:26,960
Ouch!

424
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:33,680
The Hybrid is a very dangerous secret.

425
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:36,600
A very, very dangerous secret.

426
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:39,320
And it needs to be kept locked!

427
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:41,240
(GRUNTS)

428
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:44,440
So I'm telling you nothing.

429
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:47,080
Nothing at all.

430
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:51,120
Instead, I'm gonna do
something far worse.

431
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:53,280
(GRUNTS)

432
00:39:55,520 --> 00:39:57,000
I'm gonna get out of here.

433
00:39:57,400 --> 00:40:01,960
And find whoever put me here
in the first place.

434
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:04,160
And whatever they're trying to do,

435
00:40:04,240 --> 00:40:05,760
I'm going to stop it, Clara!

436
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:06,920
(GROANS)

437
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:11,120
(EXHALES)

438
00:40:13,800 --> 00:40:15,560
It might take a little while.

439
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:18,760
Since you want me
to tell you a story.

440
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:20,720
(GRUNTS)

441
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:26,080
The Brothers Grimm,
lovely fellows.

442
00:40:26,160 --> 00:40:27,160
They're on my darts team.

443
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:28,240
(GROANS)

444
00:40:31,040 --> 00:40:32,240
According to them,

445
00:40:33,880 --> 00:40:36,320
there's this emperor,

446
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:39,200
and he asks the shepherd's boy...

447
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:44,240
"How many seconds in eternity?"

448
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:48,880
(SCREAMING)

449
00:40:51,240 --> 00:40:52,520
(FLIES BUZZING)

450
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:02,680
(STATIC)

451
00:41:22,360 --> 00:41:25,240
(TARDIS POWERING UP)

452
00:41:32,560 --> 00:41:35,200
People always get it wrong
with Time Lords.

453
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:37,880
We take forever to die.

454
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:44,160
Even if we're too injured
to regenerate,

455
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:47,200
every cell in our bodies
keeps trying.

456
00:41:48,880 --> 00:41:52,120
Dying properly can take days.

457
00:41:52,840 --> 00:41:55,440
It's why we like to die
among our own kind.

458
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:00,920
They know
not to bury us early.

459
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:02,760
(DOCTOR GROANS)

460
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:04,000
DOCTOR: I think,

461
00:42:05,120 --> 00:42:06,680
in my current condition,

462
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:09,320
it will take me about

463
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,560
a day and a half to reach
the top of the tower.

464
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:14,960
(GRUNTS)

465
00:42:17,320 --> 00:42:19,600
I think...

466
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:23,200
If I'm lucky,

467
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:25,400
I have a day and a half.

468
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:26,920
(GROANS)

469
00:42:28,040 --> 00:42:29,800
I have to do this, Clara.

470
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:33,160
It's the only way.

471
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:38,080
I have to be strong.

472
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:43,600
I should have known
from the very beginning.

473
00:42:44,760 --> 00:42:45,880
Of course.

474
00:42:47,880 --> 00:42:50,360
The portrait of you,

475
00:42:50,440 --> 00:42:52,480
the creature from
my own nightmares.

476
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:56,120
This place,

477
00:42:56,200 --> 00:42:58,440
it's my own bespoke
torture chamber.

478
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:01,960
Intended for me only.

479
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:04,960
And all those skulls

480
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:06,320
in the water,

481
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:12,360
how could there be
other prisoners in my hell?

482
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:17,200
The answer of course...

483
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:22,680
Is there were never
any other prisoners.

484
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:26,320
And the stars...

485
00:43:32,200 --> 00:43:35,040
They weren't in the wrong place.

486
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:39,120
And I haven't time travelled.

487
00:43:47,960 --> 00:43:49,840
I've just been here.

488
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:53,240
(FEEBLY) A very, very...

489
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:56,600
...long time.

490
00:43:58,960 --> 00:44:00,960
Every room resets.

491
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:02,840
Remember I told you that?

492
00:44:03,960 --> 00:44:06,760
Every room reverts
to its original condition.

493
00:44:07,920 --> 00:44:09,120
Logically,

494
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:12,280
the teleporter should do the same.

495
00:44:13,120 --> 00:44:15,720
Teleporter, fancy word.

496
00:44:16,160 --> 00:44:18,200
Just like 3D-printers, really.

497
00:44:18,960 --> 00:44:21,720
Except they break down
living matter and information,

498
00:44:21,800 --> 00:44:23,040
and transmit it.

499
00:44:23,800 --> 00:44:26,240
All you have to do is add energy.

500
00:44:28,440 --> 00:44:29,440
(GRUNTING)

501
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:32,280
The room has reset.

502
00:44:32,360 --> 00:44:34,880
Returned to its original
condition when I had arrived.

503
00:44:35,320 --> 00:44:36,520
That means...

504
00:44:37,760 --> 00:44:41,440
There's a copy of me
still in the hard drive.

505
00:44:43,640 --> 00:44:44,640
Me...

506
00:44:46,320 --> 00:44:47,920
exactly as I was

507
00:44:49,160 --> 00:44:53,840
when I first got here
7,000 years ago.

508
00:44:54,960 --> 00:44:56,400
(DOCTOR GROANS)

509
00:44:57,480 --> 00:45:01,080
DOCTOR: All I have to find
ls some energy.

510
00:45:04,040 --> 00:45:07,600
And all you need for energy

511
00:45:07,680 --> 00:45:09,280
is something to burn.

512
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:15,040
(GRUNTS)

513
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:19,360
-(GROANS)
-(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

514
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:25,240
(DOCTOR EXHALES)

515
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:54,160
DOCTOR: How long
can I keep doing this, Clara?

516
00:45:56,760 --> 00:45:58,520
Burning the old me

517
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:01,560
to make a new one.

518
00:46:02,440 --> 00:46:03,560
(TARDIS POWERING DOWN)

519
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:16,160
(COUGHING)

520
00:46:46,240 --> 00:46:48,400
DOCTOR: If you think
because she's dead I'm weak,

521
00:46:48,480 --> 00:46:50,400
then you understand very little.

522
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:54,040
If you were any part of killing her

523
00:46:54,120 --> 00:46:55,440
and you're not afraid,

524
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:57,960
then you understand
nothing at all.

525
00:46:58,040 --> 00:47:00,680
And so for your own sake
understand this.

526
00:47:00,760 --> 00:47:02,160
I'm the Doctor.

527
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:04,640
I'm coming to find you.

528
00:47:04,720 --> 00:47:06,280
And I will never ever stop.

529
00:47:06,360 --> 00:47:07,480
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

530
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:19,520
Because you won't see this coming.

531
00:47:19,600 --> 00:47:20,600
(GRUNTS)

532
00:47:39,120 --> 00:47:40,200
DOCTOR: If I didn't know better,

533
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:43,400
I'd say I travelled
7,000 years into the future.

534
00:47:48,840 --> 00:47:49,840
(GRUNTS)

535
00:47:49,920 --> 00:47:50,960
"How many seconds

536
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:53,240
"in eternity?"

537
00:47:53,360 --> 00:47:54,360
(SCREAMS)

538
00:47:56,120 --> 00:47:57,280
(GRUNTS)

539
00:48:00,680 --> 00:48:02,240
(COUGHING)

540
00:48:11,440 --> 00:48:12,960
If I didn't know better,

541
00:48:13,040 --> 00:48:15,560
I'd say I travelled
12,000 years into the future.

542
00:48:19,880 --> 00:48:20,960
(GRUNTS)

543
00:48:21,280 --> 00:48:24,080
"How many seconds
in eternity?”

544
00:48:25,080 --> 00:48:26,160
The shepherd's boy...

545
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:27,520
(SCREAMS)

546
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:29,640
(COUGHING)

547
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:35,560
(SCREAMING)

548
00:48:35,640 --> 00:48:37,480
Six hundred thousand years
into the future.

549
00:48:37,920 --> 00:48:38,960
(SCREAMS)

550
00:48:39,040 --> 00:48:40,960
"How many seconds
in eternity?”

551
00:48:41,840 --> 00:48:43,400
The shepherd's boy says...

552
00:48:43,600 --> 00:48:44,600
(SCREAMS)

553
00:48:45,320 --> 00:48:46,360
(COUGHING)

554
00:48:53,080 --> 00:48:55,040
Twelve hundred thousand years
into the future.

555
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:56,360
(GROANS)

556
00:48:57,080 --> 00:48:58,720
And the shepherd's boy says...

557
00:49:00,200 --> 00:49:01,200
(COUGHING)

558
00:49:02,640 --> 00:49:04,400
Two million years into the future.

559
00:49:07,600 --> 00:49:09,480
And the shepherd's boy says...

560
00:49:10,240 --> 00:49:11,240
(COUGHING)

561
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:20,200
(SHRIEKING)

562
00:49:25,960 --> 00:49:27,720
Twenty million years
into the future.

563
00:49:29,720 --> 00:49:30,880
Ow!

564
00:49:31,080 --> 00:49:33,280
And the shepherd's boy says...

565
00:49:33,440 --> 00:49:34,440
(GRUNTS)

566
00:49:34,600 --> 00:49:36,800
"There's this mountain
of pure diamond.

567
00:49:37,280 --> 00:49:39,240
"It takes an hour to climb it.

568
00:49:39,320 --> 00:49:41,720
"And an hour to go around it."

569
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:44,120
(COUGHING)

570
00:49:54,200 --> 00:49:55,840
Fifty-two million years.

571
00:49:57,320 --> 00:49:59,080
"Every hundred years,

572
00:49:59,160 --> 00:50:00,800
"a little bird comes.

573
00:50:02,160 --> 00:50:05,120
"It sharpens its beak
on the diamond mountain."”

574
00:50:06,200 --> 00:50:07,360
(COUGHING)

575
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:13,560
Nearly a billion years.

576
00:50:13,800 --> 00:50:14,800
(GRUNTS)

577
00:50:15,520 --> 00:50:17,800
"And when the entire mountain
is chiselled away,

578
00:50:17,880 --> 00:50:20,480
"the first second in eternity

579
00:50:20,560 --> 00:50:21,560
"will have passed.”

580
00:50:21,760 --> 00:50:22,760
(SCREAMS)

581
00:50:23,600 --> 00:50:24,640
(COUGHING)

582
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:27,120
Well over a billion years.

583
00:50:27,200 --> 00:50:28,200
(GRUNTS)

584
00:50:28,560 --> 00:50:30,480
You must think
that's a hell of a long time.

585
00:50:31,720 --> 00:50:32,840
(COUGHING)

586
00:50:33,240 --> 00:50:34,400
Two billion years.

587
00:50:34,720 --> 00:50:35,720
(GRUNTS)

588
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:37,880
Personally,

589
00:50:37,960 --> 00:50:39,160
I think that's a hell of a...

590
00:50:39,480 --> 00:50:40,520
(COUGHING)

591
00:50:41,080 --> 00:50:42,240
(YELLS)

592
00:50:43,120 --> 00:50:44,640
(CRACKING)

593
00:50:51,320 --> 00:50:52,320
(EXHALES)

594
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:01,520
Personally,

595
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:03,760
I think that's a hell of a bird.

596
00:51:06,160 --> 00:51:07,840
(LOUD THUD)

597
00:51:07,920 --> 00:51:10,440
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

598
00:51:19,440 --> 00:51:20,760
(WHOOSHING)

599
00:51:49,080 --> 00:51:51,200
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

600
00:51:58,040 --> 00:52:01,080
Go to the city,
find somebody important,

601
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:02,880
tell them I'm back.

602
00:52:03,760 --> 00:52:06,200
Tell them
I know what they did.

603
00:52:06,760 --> 00:52:08,400
And I'm on my way.

604
00:52:09,680 --> 00:52:12,360
And if they ask you who I am,

605
00:52:12,440 --> 00:52:14,920
tell them I came
the long way around.

606
00:52:35,200 --> 00:52:37,080
You can probably
still hear me.

607
00:52:38,640 --> 00:52:40,680
So just between ourselves,

608
00:52:41,920 --> 00:52:43,680
you've got the prophecy wrong.

609
00:52:44,800 --> 00:52:46,800
The Hybrid is not half Dalek.

610
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:48,160
Nothing is half Dalek.

611
00:52:48,240 --> 00:52:50,120
The Daleks
would never allow that.

612
00:52:50,200 --> 00:52:53,680
The Hybrid destined
to conquer Gallifrey

613
00:52:53,760 --> 00:52:55,640
and stand in its ruins...

614
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:02,000
...Is me.

615
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:05,880
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

616
00:53:33,240 --> 00:53:34,240
ASHILDR: 7he Hybrid...

617
00:53:34,320 --> 00:53:35,840
I think it's time to tell the truth.

618
00:53:35,920 --> 00:53:37,840
WOMAN: I heard the Doctor
had come home.

619
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:39,440
One so loves fireworks.

620
00:53:39,520 --> 00:53:41,320
MAN: What's he up to?

621
00:53:41,400 --> 00:53:45,600
The Hybrid is a creature thought to be
cross-bred from two warrior races.

622
00:53:45,880 --> 00:53:47,120
I know I went too far.

623
00:53:47,360 --> 00:53:50,120
You have broken every code
you ever lived by.

624
00:53:50,200 --> 00:53:51,320
On my command!

625
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:52,520
ASHILDR: Is it true?

626
00:53:52,960 --> 00:53:54,000
DOCTOR: She's my friend.

627
00:53:54,080 --> 00:53:55,080
-(LASER FIRE)
-(DOCTOR SCREAMING)

628
00:53:55,160 --> 00:53:57,320
Red Team to Sector 52,
extraction chamber 7.

629
00:53:57,400 --> 00:53:58,600
Regeneration in progress.

